SIMPLE: capitulation
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Capitulation
<hw>Ca*pit`u*la"tion</hw>
<pr>(k⟦adot⟧*p⟦icr⟧t`⟦usl⟧*l⟦amac⟧"sh⟦ucr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Cf. F. <ets>capitulation</ets>, LL. <ets>capitulatio</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A reducing to heads or articles; a formal
agreement.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With special <qex>capitulation</qex> that neither the Scots nor
the French shall refortify.</q> <rj><qau>Bp. Burnet.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The act of capitulating or surrendering to an enemy
upon stipulated terms.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The instrument containing the terms of an agreement
or surrender.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Capitulator</ent>⟦br⟧
